        <outline text="Back to WorkFlowy " _note="Naomi: https://workflowy.com/s/shared/F7SeDfERAvwaBSW8&#xA;EP: [https://workflowy.com/#/1e8a0bee6fec](https://workflowy.com/#/1e8a0bee6fec)"/>
        <outline text="Projects">
            <outline text="Practical Exercises">
                <outline text="Practical 1 - LSB Embedding Steganography Exercise" heading="2">
                    <outline text="This workshop gives an insight into a basic steganographic cover-modification technique called LSB Embedding (Least Significant Bit Embedding). The primary learning objective is to become familiar with the basic elements of a steganographic system, via the practical task of hiding secret bits within an image file that will serve as a cover-medium. "/>
                    <outline text="Step 1 - Download and unzip the practical resources" checkbox="true" heading="3" colorLabel="6">
                        <outline text="a) Locate the file “steganography_practicals.zip” and download it to the root of your H: or USB drive and unzip the file."/>
                        <outline text="b) Download HxD Hex Editor from https://download.cnet.com/HxD-Hex-Editor/3000-2352_4-10891068.html"/>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="Step 2 - Define the secret data" checkbox="true" heading="3" colorLabel="5">
                        <outline text="a) Decide on a single word that will represent your secret. Ideally, choose a word of no more than 5 characters."/>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="Step 3 - Determine the ASCII and binary values for each character of secret word" checkbox="true" heading="3" colorLabel="4">
                        <outline text="Find the ASCII and corresponding binary values for each character of your secret word. This can be found at sites such as http://easycalculation.com/ascii-hex.php  "/>
                        <outline text="Note the binary equivalent of each individual letter of your word (If your secret word includes letters with different cases, be sure to note that upper and lower case characters have different ASCII values and will therefore have different binary values)"/>
                        <outline text="E.g.:   ![Example](https://dynalist.io/u/vSeAPlpu_4MRRAhM7nteKATh)  "/>
                        <outline text="Q: What is the total length of your secret word in bits? "/>
                        <outline text="Q: How many bytes of data will be required to embed your secret word in the cover-image? "/>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="Step 4 - Defining the cover-image" checkbox="true" heading="3" colorLabel="3">
                        <outline text="Read and understand the following:"/>
                        <outline text="The cover-image selected for this practical is a windows bitmap image file. Bitmap files have a data structure that is well suited to illustrating the concepts of LSB embedding. The RGB (Red, Green, Blue) data of bitmap files is uncompressed and is easily accessible with a hex editor. "/>
                        <outline text="Basic BMP data structure:">
                            <outline text="The bitmap file structure is comprised of three core sections: BITMAPFILEHEADER, BITMAPINFOHEADER, BITMAPDATA "/>
                            <outline text="Table 1 details the structure of each section and defines the offset, size, and description of data fields. The columns titled “Hex Value” and “Value” are populated with sample data to indicate typical values. "/>
                            <outline text="  ![Table 1](https://dynalist.io/u/Jwoy5vYu5bdm0LxecFpGzcn2) "/>
                        </outline>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="Step 5 - Creating a carrier-image" checkbox="true" heading="3" colorLabel="2">
                        <outline text="a) Navigate to the steganography_practicals/practical_1/cover_medium folder in your home directory:" checkbox="true">
                            <outline text="i) Select an image that you will use as a cover-image"/>
                            <outline text="ii) Duplicate this image and rename this copied file to carrier-image.bmp"/>
                        </outline>
                        <outline text="b) Open HxD:">
                            <outline text="i) Navigate to File, Open, select carrier-image.bmp, Open"/>
                            <outline text="ii) A hexadecimal view of the file will open in the main window of HxD as illustrated here:                      ![Hexadecimal view](https://dynalist.io/u/Q7dUUt1UQIavqMMmKvxtzFg1) "/>
                            <outline text="For clarity, the LSB embedding process will start from offset 0x36. Recall from the data structure outlined earlier in this practical that offset 0x36 is where the structure for the RGB pixel data begins. It is in the raw pixel data that the bits of your secret word bits will be embedded."/>
                            <outline text="iii) Highlight offset 0x36                                                   ![Offset 0x36](https://dynalist.io/u/lgZWb1_m1x7WJ7Svgo_NcuyC)                                                                                      The byte at offset 0x36 will be the first in a sequence that will have its least significant bits modified"/>
                            <outline text="iv) Refer to the binary equivelant of each letter of your word noted previously and look at the first bit of the first letter, if this matches the least significant bit of offset 0x36, leave it as it is, if it does not, change it to match the first bit of the first letter          ![Least Significant Bit](https://dynalist.io/u/ea9gP-iMp67uM2CxK4tk5qP2) "/>
                            <outline text="v) Navigate to offset 0x37  and change the least significant bit of offset 0x37 if needed to match the second bit of the first letter                                              ![Offset 0x37](https://dynalist.io/u/QANmpXOS-qZoCqMCCoveg_OW) "/>
                            <outline text="vi) Repeat this process until you reach the end of the word "/>
                            <outline text="vii) Save and close HxD"/>
                        </outline>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="Step 6 - Visually compare the original image and the carrier-image" checkbox="true" heading="3" colorLabel="1">
                        <outline text="Use Windows Photo Viewer or an alternate application to compare your original cover-image and your carrier-image to see if you can visually detect differences"/>
                    </outline>
                </outline>
                <outline text="Practical 2 - StegJ" heading="2">
                    <outline text="Background" heading="3">
                        <outline text="The application was written by Francesca Camagni and is released under a GPL license. The project is hosted at: http://sourceforge.net/projects/stegj/. The project home page located at http://stegj.sourceforge.net."/>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="Objectives" heading="3">
                        <outline text="The primary learning objective is to contextualise the manual LSB embedding process experienced in Practical 1, against the use of a dedicated steganography application to complete a similar task of hiding secret data within a cover-image."/>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="Part 1" checkbox="true" heading="3" colorLabel="6">
                        <outline text="Step 1 - Define the secret data">
                            <outline text="a) Navigate to the steganography_practicals/practical_2/steganography/secret_data_created folder on your H: drive."/>
                            <outline text="b) Open the file “secret.txt” and write a secret message"/>
                            <outline text="c) Save the file"/>
                        </outline>
                        <outline text="Step 2 - Create a carrier-image">
                            <outline text="a) Navigate to the steganography_practicals/practical_2/StegJ folder on your H: drive:">
<outline text="i) Locate and run the file stegj_v0.2beta.jar to start the StegJ application"/>
<outline text="ii) The application should load and appear as follows:                                                                           ![Figure 1](https://dynalist.io/u/0GAhLPihbplU20OxlQj6cka1)  "/>
<outline text="iii) Right click the curser in the &quot;Cover Image&quot; field"/>
<outline text="iv) Navigate to the steganography_practicals/practical_2/steganography/cover_medium folder on your H: drive and select a file to use as a cover-image                ![Figure 2](https://dynalist.io/u/PVOwwDRVOscnJCCQyy0pItp4) "/>
<outline text="v) Right click the curser on the &quot;File to Embed&quot; field"/>
<outline text="vi) Navigate to the steganography_practicals/practical_2/steganography/secret_data_created folder on your H: drive and select the file “secret.txt” as the “File to Embed” and click open"/>
<outline text="vii) Right click the curser on the &quot;Output Image&quot; field "/>
<outline text="viii) Navigate to the steganography_practicals/practical_2/steganography/stego_medium folder on your H: drive. "/>
<outline text="ix) In the file name, type &quot;carrier-image&quot;  and click save                                                                       ![Figure 3](https://dynalist.io/u/K8V7K5fULEDzoeAqVqwPLe9w) "/>
<outline text="x) Click Embed                                                             ![Figure 4](https://dynalist.io/u/X_UY7chVR86HXf7AHf-bsnlj) "/>
<outline text="xi) A &quot;File Embedded Successfully&quot; message should then appear, click ok (don't close StegJ)                                                   ![Figure 5](https://dynalist.io/u/QNnl-LxfXdrrJ1qadQPWfES9) "/>
                            </outline>
                        </outline>
                        <outline text="Step 3 - Reveal the secret data">
                            <outline text="a) Click the &quot;Retrive data&quot; tab                                         ![Figure 6](https://dynalist.io/u/cEHWpeewnOycijQcGw0yDLPT) "/>
                            <outline text="b) Right click the curser in the &quot;image&quot; field:">
<outline text="i) Navigate to the steganography_practicals/practical_2/steganography/stego_medium folder on your H: drive."/>
<outline text="ii) Select the file “carrier-image” and click open"/>
                            </outline>
                            <outline text="c) Right click the curser in the &quot;Output path&quot; field:">
<outline text="i) Navigate to the steganography_practicals/practical_2/steganography/secret_data_revealed folder on your H: drive"/>
<outline text="ii) Click save  ![Figure 7](https://dynalist.io/u/NqQ41aSK1SOjA5VOrKPWVEcg) "/>
<outline text="iii) Click on the &quot;Retrive Hidden Data&quot; button  ![Figure 8](https://dynalist.io/u/4XsBjPjq8ex78wbeZAMb4QUd) "/>
<outline text="iv) A notification should appear stating that the secret data has been extracted to the selected folder. Click ok                                                                            ![Figure 9](https://dynalist.io/u/aZTcjO27zcFtPlyt3Tmp5L2g) "/>
                            </outline>
                            <outline text="d) Navigate to the steganography_practicals/practical_2/secret_data_revealed folder on your H: drive to view the file"/>
                            <outline text="e) Experiment with alternative file formats as cover-mediums and secret data as well as selecting other application settings.  "/>
                            <outline text="Question: What happens if the secret data is too large to be hidden in the cover-medium?"/>
                        </outline>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="Part 2" checkbox="true" heading="3" colorLabel="5">
                        <outline text="Share carrier image">
                            <outline text="a) Create a new carrier-image"/>
                            <outline text="b) Confirm that the secret data can be successfully retrieved"/>
                            <outline text="c) Share this carrier-image with another student"/>
                            <outline text="d) Retrieve the secret data from the carrier-image that you receive"/>
                        </outline>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="Part 3" checkbox="true" heading="3" colorLabel="4">
                        <outline text="Rotate image ">
                            <outline text="a) Create a new carrier-image and call it &quot;original-carrier-image&quot;"/>
                            <outline text="b) Download GIMP if you don't already have it https://www.gimp.org/downloads/"/>
                            <outline text="b) Set up and run GIMP"/>
                            <outline text="c) From the GIMP main menu: File, Open and navigate to your original-carrier-image.ext. Highlight it and click the Open button."/>
                            <outline text="d) From the GIMP main menu: Image, Transform, Rotate 180o                                                                          ![Rotate](https://dynalist.io/u/gUHKAiijzWqXUm_v_IrrmHEa) "/>
                            <outline text="e) Save the file as &quot;carrier-image-rotate&quot;"/>
                            <outline text="f) From the GIMP main menu: File, Close "/>
                        </outline>
                        <outline text="Resize image">
                            <outline text="a) From the GIMP main menu: File, Open and navigate to your original-carrier-image.ext (where (ext) is the file format). Highlight it and click the Open button."/>
                            <outline text="b) From the GIMP main menu: Image, Scale Image:">
<outline text="i) In the Width field enter a smaller or larger value"/>
<outline text="ii) Click the Scale button                                           ![Scale](https://dynalist.io/u/KUvnRcET1nK8ZH8dJ3tNx2Vi) "/>
                            </outline>
                            <outline text="c) Save the file as &quot;carrier-image-scale&quot;"/>
                            <outline text="d) From the GIMP main menu: File, Close "/>
                        </outline>
                        <outline text="Crop image">
                            <outline text="a) From the GIMP main menu: File, Open and navigate to your original-carrier-image.ext. Highlight it and click the Open button."/>
                            <outline text="b) From the GIMP main menu: Tools, Transform Tools, Crop:">
<outline text="i) Using the mouse, drag a rectangular crop window that excludes the edges of the image.                                           ![Cropping](https://dynalist.io/u/fzpOEZtx6doA2FkEkyALf0HU) "/>
<outline text="ii) Click the image to apply the crop. The area within the crop box remains. The area outside of the crop box disappears.                                            ![Cropped](https://dynalist.io/u/fgZndswDsITqEFUMl7ZGB0G4) "/>
                            </outline>
                            <outline text="c) Save the file as &quot;carrier-image-crop&quot;"/>
                            <outline text="d) From the GIMP main menu: File, Close "/>
                        </outline>
                        <outline text="Hue and Saturation ">
                            <outline text="a) From the GIMP main menu: File, Open and navigate to your original-carrier-image.ext. Highlight it and click the Open button."/>
                            <outline text="b) From the GIMP main menu: Colours, Hue-Saturation:">
<outline text="i) Adjust the Hue, Lightness and Saturation sliders and click the OK button                               ![Hue-Saturation](https://dynalist.io/u/LjblNt3-YmRpT9C1zTPDYTOo) "/>
                            </outline>
                            <outline text="c) Save the file as &quot;carrier-image-hue-saturation&quot;"/>
                            <outline text="d) From the GIMP main menu: File, Close"/>
                        </outline>
                        <outline text="Your own choice of image modification ">
                            <outline text="a) From the GIMP main menu: File, Open and navigate to your original-carrier-image.ext. Highlight it and click the Open button."/>
                            <outline text="b) Select an image modification of your own choice"/>
                            <outline text="c) Save the file as carrier-image-my-modication.ext. (where my-modification reflects the change you have made"/>
                            <outline text="d) From the GIMP main menu: File, Close "/>
                        </outline>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="Part 4" checkbox="true" heading="3" colorLabel="3">
                        <outline text="Carrier image robustness test:">
                            <outline text="Use StegJ to open each of your modified stego-images that were created in Part 3 of this practical. Determine which of the modifications did not affect the ability to retrieve the secret data. "/>
                        </outline>
                    </outline>
